The paper deals with complexity results for problems related to graphs and their subgraphs, which are common topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of these problems, which falls under computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper involves the study of independent sets, which is a topic in combinatorics (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the well-covered property of graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG).
